The paper proposes a model-based reinforcement learning technique that uses Monte-Carlo tree search (MCTS) and provides sample complexity bounds for a tree search-based RL algorithm. This suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a deep neural network implementation, which indicates that it could also belong to the cs.LG sub-category. The paper's focus on decision-making and optimization suggests that it could also belong to the cs.GT sub-category. The use of MCTS and the iterative refinement of the leaf-node evaluator suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.SY sub-category. Finally, the paper's application to a popular online game suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO sub-category.
